<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="335" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d335">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1488.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Commissioner <persName type="from">Fort</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Santo Domingo</hi></placeName>, <lb/>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-21">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 21, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Conference tomorrow for selection of Provisional President with Bordas,
                            Vasquez, Jiménez, Vidal and Velásquez represented. Small leaders will
                            speak through them. All armed activities have ceased. The outlook for
                            agreement tomorrow good. Expect to wire name of Provisional President
                            for your advice tomorrow and if approved induct him into office on
                            Monday if possible.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Fort</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>